<div data-collapse="accordion" id="faq">			
			<h2><div class="dashicons dashicons-editor-help"></div><?php _e('Can I also paste my shortcode into Widgets or Category Descriptions?', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></h2>
			<div class="content"><div class="dashicons dashicons-yes"></div>
			<p><?php _e('By default, WordPress only allows shortcodes in posts and pages.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p><p><?php _e('But hey! Look below! Just enable the settings below to use FTG anywhere you like.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			</div>
			
			<h2><div class="dashicons dashicons-editor-help"></div><?php _e('I want to create my own template. How do I do that?', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></h2>
			<div class="content"><div class="dashicons dashicons-yes"></div>
			<p><?php _e('Go to <a href="http://foothumbnails.mattcromwell.com/" target="_blank">the FTG website</a> which covers this plugin in detail and has several different custom templates you can download.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			<p><?php _e('Customize the template however you like, name it "foothumbnail-template.php", and drop it into your theme folder. Then when you create a new Gallery, select "Custom" on Step 5 and you\'re custom template will be used.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			</div>
			
			<h2><div class="dashicons dashicons-editor-help"></div><?php _e('I don\'t have FooBox, where can I get it?', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></h2>
			<div class="content"><div class="dashicons dashicons-yes"></div>
			<p><?php _e('Excellent question! If you don\'t have either version of FooBox installed, then there should be a really big alert at the top of the screen now. It has links to download FooBox Free Image Lightbox (just for images, which is perfect for FTG), and for the really awesome, powerpacked premium version. If you don\'t see that alert, something\'s wrong, so here\'s the links again:', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			<ul>
			<li><a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/foobox-image-lightbox/" target="_blank">FooBox Free Image Lightbox</li>
			<li><a href="http://fooplugins.com/plugins/foobox/?ref=3" target="_blank">FooBox Media Lightbox (Premium)</a></li>
			</ul>
			</div>
			
			<h2><div class="dashicons dashicons-editor-help"></div><?php _e('I like FooBox, but I don\'t understand the licenses.' , 'foothumbgallery'); ?></h2>
			<div class="content"><div class="dashicons dashicons-yes"></div>
			<p><?php _e('The short version is that you are paying for updates and premium support for one year. A Personal license gives you that for 1 domain, Multi for 5, and Business for unlimited. For full details, <a href="http://fooplugins.com/licensing/">read here</a>.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			</div>			
			
			<h2><div class="dashicons dashicons-editor-help"></div><?php _e('FTG is pretty cool! What made you want to build this?', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></h2>
			<div class="content"><div class="dashicons dashicons-yes"></div>
			<p><?php _e('As the Solutions Manager for FooPlugins, I received a lot of feedback from FooBox users wanting to implement the "hidden Gallery" feature, but struggled either because they had A LOT of galleries and coding it manually took a lot of time, or they simply were not used to having to insert html code into their pages. I received the same feedback from personal clients of mine who just didn\'t want to hassle with it.', 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			<p><?php _e('So I thought up this idea, discovered a few great resources and decided to try my hand at my very first public plugin. I\'m pretty happy with the results. You can read my full post all about it <a href="http://mattcromwell.com/introducing-foothumbnails" target="_blank">here</a>.' , 'foothumbgallery'); ?></p>
			</div>